                            <comment id="13668647" author="elyograg" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 20:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to fix the issue.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shalin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;shalin&quot;&gt;shalin&lt;/a&gt;, the CHANGES.txt entry is under 4.3.1, so I&apos;d like to know whether it&apos;s OK to backport.  If not, I&apos;ll move that to 4.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668657" author="elyograg" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 20:49:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Something related, not sure whether it&apos;s worth fixing: If you change the logging level to WARN (or below) on something low level like org (or the root, after this patch), you don&apos;t get anything in the log about changing the level - because the log entry about the change is INFO.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668731" author="hossman" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 22:15:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 - patch looks clean and correct to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As discussed with shawn on IRC, JulWatcher has similar code, but that seems to be correct - most likely this bug stemmed from the JulWatcher code being copied/modified to create the Log4jWatcher&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
